# finn-agent — runtime secrets template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy to .env and fill in real values:   cp .env.sample .env && chmod 600 .env
# .env is gitignored (*.env) — NEVER commit it.
#
# setup-finn.sh reads all of this in one idempotent pass (it auto-sources ./.env; you
# can also `set -a; . ./.env; set +a` first). Each layer runs only if its keys are set:
#   telegram . TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN          search ... BRAVE_API_KEY
#   fetch .... FIRECRAWL_API_KEY           models ... INFERENCE_MODEL_ID (+ optional OPENROUTER_API_KEY)
#   calendar . MS_CALENDAR_CLIENT_ID + MS_CALENDAR_REFRESH_TOKEN
#   notion ... NOTION_TOKEN                radar .... NOTION_TOKEN
# (MOONSHOT_API_KEY is consumed at `nemoclaw onboard` by the gateway provider, not by setup-finn.sh.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- NVIDIA inference -------------------------------------------------------
# NVIDIA API key for the Nemotron managed inference route. From build.nvidia.com.
NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- Alternate model providers ----------------------------------------------
# Moonshot AI (Kimi) API key — backs the HOST gateway's 'compatible-endpoint'
# provider (base URL https://api.moonshot.ai/v1), which the sandbox reaches as
# inference.local. Registered at `nemoclaw onboard` (provider: "Other
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint"); the key never enters the sandbox. platform.kimi.ai.
MOONSHOT_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# The sandbox's inference primary = inference/$INFERENCE_MODEL_ID, served by whatever
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint you register HOST-side at onboard. To move to another
# provider/model, edit these two + re-run  ONLY='models' ./setup-finn.sh  (the endpoint
# URL here is informational — the live URL + its API key are entered at `nemoclaw onboard`).
# setup-finn.sh also rewrites the baked model-pin ARG defaults in Dockerfile.finn-2026.6.10
# from these values on every run (sync_dockerfile_pin) — THIS file is the single place a
# model is named; don't edit the Dockerfile ARGs by hand (LEARNINGS §6/§12).
#   e.g. OpenRouter AS THE PRIMARY (also OpenAI-compatible):
#     INFERENCE_ENDPOINT_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
#     INFERENCE_MODEL_ID=moonshotai/kimi-k2.6   # OpenRouter's <author>/<slug>
#   ...and at onboard paste that URL + your OpenRouter key as the "Other OpenAI-compatible
#   endpoint". That is the COMPATIBLE-ENDPOINT path (key host-side, sandbox posture unchanged).
INFERENCE_ENDPOINT_URL=https://api.moonshot.ai/v1
INFERENCE_MODEL_ID=kimi-k2.6
# ⚠️ DISTINCT mechanism: OPENROUTER_API_KEY below wires OpenRouter as OpenClaw's built-in
# *fallback* provider (openrouter/<author>/<slug>, key injected INTO the sandbox config +
# the fixes/openrouter.yaml egress preset — a DIRECT gateway-netns call). Use it for the
# fallback route; use the INFERENCE_* vars above to make OpenRouter the primary. (sk-or-...)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- Telegram channel -------------------------------------------------------
# Bot token from @BotFather, format <digits>:<secret>. Consumed by the
# interactive `nemoclaw finn channels add telegram` (baked into the image at rebuild).
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=0000000000:AAxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Your numeric Telegram user id (from @userinfobot) — DM target / allowlist.
TELEGRAM_USER_ID=000000000

# --- Web search + fetch -----------------------------------------------------
# Brave Search API key (search provider; injected by onboard). brave.com/search/api
BRAVE_API_KEY=BSxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Firecrawl API key for full-page web_fetch. firecrawl.dev. Optional (omit = search-only).
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=fc-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- Calendar layer (Outlook / live.com via MCP) ----------------------------
# Azure app (client) id for the device-code MS Graph flow. portal.azure.com → App registrations.
MS_CALENDAR_CLIENT_ID='00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000'
# Delegated MS Graph refresh token minted by tools/ms-graph-login.mjs (scope Calendars.ReadWrite).
MS_CALENDAR_REFRESH_TOKEN='M.C5xx_xxxx.0.U.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'
# Calendar write tools (create/update/delete_event) — explicit opt-in; 0/omit = read-only.
MS_CALENDAR_WRITE=1

# --- Notion connector + conference radar ------------------------------------
# Notion internal integration token (ntn_...). notion.so/my-integrations.
NOTION_TOKEN=ntn_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Notion write tools (create_page/update_page/append_blocks) — explicit opt-in; 0/omit =
# read-only. ⚠️ The radar cron loops REQUIRE write mode (they update cadence columns +
# create snapshot rows): without this a plain `./setup-finn.sh` re-run after a rebuild
# silently drops Notion to read-only and every radar run reports "Notion tools blocked".
NOTION_WRITE=1
